Nigeria’s president Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday evening make a nationwide broadcast to the nation. “President Buhari will Thursday broadcast to the nation at 7 pm with a repeat at 9 pm,” said Buhari’s spokesperson, Garba Shehu. “All television, radio stations and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the @NTANewsNow and Radio Nigeria for the broadcast,” he added. The reason for the broadcast is yet to be ascertained.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .